

=Bio=


"Andrea Goetzke is curator, consultant and organizer, and one of the owners and project leads of the Berlin-based agency newthinking communications (newthinking-communications.de).

She explores open approaches to production and social organization in various ways, and is interested in new models and experiments for a culturally rich and diverse society. 

For example:

Andrea initiated and organized the openeverything events in Berlin (openeverything.mixxt.de/), conducted workshops on topics like open design, or collaborated on a programme to promote open source software skills in African countries. She is curator and board member of the all2gethernow (www.a-2-n.de), convention for new strategies in music and culture, and hosts a monthly free culture radio show on reboot.fm.

At the Berlin Commons Conference, she aims to interview participants and report on the conference for the blog netzpolitik.org."



